item.title: [+2390] Google to offer 'ultra high-speed' broadband in US
item.description: Google is spreading its wings in yet another direction - this time as a network provider, offering super-fast broadband to thousands of US homes. It plans to build a fiber-optic network offering speeds of up to 1Gbps (gigabit per second) to up to 500,000 homes.

item.title: [+2054] 'Deadliest Catch' Captain Phil Harris Dies
item.description: Breaking: Captain Phil Harris has died. The Seattle-based skipper of the Cornelia Marie suffered a stroke two weeks ago was recently placed in a medically induced coma to reduce brain swelling. Even though many reports say he was improving, Phil has passed away...

item.title: [+1453] Mocking Palin, Obama spokesman writes grocery list on hand
item.description: Among the items written on his hand, he said, were "eggs, milk" and "bread." He said he'd crossed off "toast." White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs was responding to reports this past weekend that Palin had written a "cheat sheet" on her hand -- despite criticizing Obama for using teleprompters at the same event.

item.title: [+799] New Opera App for iPhone 6X Faster, Reduces Data Cost by 90%
